@ digital signature

A message (of digital data) can be digitally signed.
-
Such a signature serves three purposes
  • It proves who has signed the message (→ development/security/authentication)
  • The signer cannot deny having signed the message (non-repudiation)
  • The recipient can be sure that the message was not altered by a third party (integrity)

